The paper discusses the generalization of deep neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. The use of information theory and Fisher information matrix suggests that the paper may belong to cs.IT. The mention of random matrix theory and the study of the parameter space suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.LG. The use of the term "neuromanifold" suggests that the paper may belong to cs.NE. The mention of deep learning and the use of minimum description length suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.AI. Finally, the mention of the Fisher information matrix and its role in improving generalization suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.CV.
